{
  "stem": "21731.2",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And she moved with two suitcases and, I think, 400 shillings to Lwow, where her family got her, in the meantime, a little flat.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And she settled down quite nicely.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "She even visited us in Lwow-- in Lublin and heard about our plans to go to Warsaw.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And she was quite for it because Lublin was not really the place to be.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So in, in spring '39, all that happened-- this moving again.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We found also a flat in Zoliborz, which was a kind of like Chiswick in, in London, a district of Warsaw.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We found a flat which was just being built.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "There were no new buildings getting up.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I looked after the arrangements there.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "My husband looked after the installment-- the institution-- [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] institute.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And Jan was in a, a school camp near Warsaw.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It was the beginning of the school holidays.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "We found also a very good school for Jan that was-- the cause also to move because Lublin had no schools for Jewish children.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "A higher school was-- they, they were not accepted, Jewish children.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So-- and we lived in two rooms, rented rooms, went out for meals.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "There was no question, I suppose.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Breakfast I  made at home.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And one day, we got a telephone-- a telegram that Milek, my brother-in-law, had a heart attack and could Max come and help out before-- till they find somebody to take over.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "So he left me in charge of everything and went to Lwow.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And that was-- must have been July.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "After two or three weeks-- Jan was very happy in this camp, in the summer camp with all his friends and very, very nice.",
      "word_count": 24
    }
  ],
